-- Ontario Teachers' Hires Scotiabank's Rowe as Head of Private Equity Unit
-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2010-10-01T11:51:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/ontario-teachers-hires-scotiabank-s-rowe-as-head-of-private-equity-unit.html
Ontario Teachers’ Pension Plan,
Canada’s third-biggest retirement fund manager, hired Bank of
Nova Scotia executive  Jane Rowe  to head its private-equity unit.  Rowe, Scotiabank’s executive vice-president of special
accounts management and retail credit risk, will join the
Toronto-based pension fund manager on Oct. 18, Teachers’ said in
an internal memo. She replaces Erol Uzumeri, who left Teachers’
in May. Scotiabank is Canada’s third-biggest bank by assets.  To contact the reporter on this story:
